# NEO4J GRAPH DATABASE DOCUMENTATION



Presently Neo4j graph database pulls &#39;event&#39; index data from kafka.

**GRAPH MODEL**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**NODES**

We store 7 types of nodes which have various properties as listed:

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **1.**** CI**

Each CI node has one property:

- cid -  cid of that particular ci.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,) **           **![](data:image/*;base64,)





1. **2.**** Event**

Each Event node has two properties:

- eventUUID – uuid of that particular event.
- TimeCreated – timestamp at which the event was created.





 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **3.**** Event Type**

Each event id node has one property:

- Id – Id of that particular event.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **4.**** Priority**

Each Priority node has one property:

- value – Priority value.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **5.**** Business Impact**

Each Business Impact node has one property:

- value -  Business Impact value.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **6.**** Application**

Each Application node has one property:

- App\_Name – Name of that particular application.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. **7.**** Scenario**

Each Scenario node has one property:

- scenarioID – scenario id of that particular scenario.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)















**RELATIONSHIPS**

We have a total of 8 types of relationships of form (node) - [relationship] -\&gt; (node):

**1. (Event) - [BELONGS\_TO] -\&gt; (Scenario)**


 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**2. (Event) - [HAS\_IMPACT] -\&gt; (BusinessImpact)**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**3. (Event) - [HAS\_PRIORITY] -\&gt; (Priority)**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**4. (Event) - [HAS\_TYPE] -\&gt; (EventType)**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**5. (Event) - [OCCURRED\_ON] -\&gt; (CI)**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**6. (Event) - [ABOUT\_CI] -\&gt; (CI)**.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**7. (CI) - [HAS] -\&gt; (Application)**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

**8. (CI) - [HOSTS] -\&gt; (CI)**
